<TITLE> Seventh Wage Board formed for journalists, employees </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 26 (bdnews24.com) -- The caretaker administration Tuesday formed the seventh Wage Board with retired High Court judge Habibur Rahman Khan as chairman for journalists and press employees. The seventh Wage Board will review its predecessor's awards and announce the revised award following discussions with related parties. The board will submit its recommendations to the caretaker government in two months from now. The board will also recommend that newspapers which do not implement their recommendations get a zero-tariff facility when importing newsprint, and other benefits including advertisements. The other eight member of the board are: Prothom Alo editor Motiur Rahman, Jugantor editor Golam Sarwar, The Independent publisher and editor Mahbubul Alam, Bangladesh Sangbad Sangstha managing director and chief editor Jaglul Ahmed Chowdhury. Journalists-Workers-Employees Unity Council member secretary Ruhul Amin Gazi, co-convenor of the Council Manzurul Ahsan Bulbul and Council members Abul Hashem and Khairul Islam. Information ministry deputy secretary Khurshid Alam will be secretary of the board, with the ministry providing secretarial assistance. bd
